This paper deals with the problem of large multi-class classification, which is a common topic in machine learning. The paper proposes a new end-to-end model called Deep Stochastic Neural Codes (DSNC) that learns to associate binary codes with categories and map inputs to binary codes. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
